    "## 3️⃣ Attention Pooling (replaces mean pooling)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Problem with mean pooling**: All 500 audio frames contribute equally. Laughter bursts are brief (~0.3-1s) and surrounded by silence/speech.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Attention pooling**: Learns a soft weighting over time steps, attending more to frames with laughter-like acoustic patterns.\n",
    "\n",
    "Mathematically:\n",
    "```\n",
    "attention_scores = softmax(Linear(hidden_dim, 1)(H))   # (T,)\n",
    "weighted_hidden  = attention_scores.unsqueeze(-1) * H   # (T, hidden_dim)\n",
    "pooled           = weighted_hidden.sum(dim=0)             # (hidden_dim,)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "This is differentiable — backprop trains the attention to find laughter-relevant frames."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class AttentionPooling(torch.nn.Module):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Differentiable attention-based pooling over sequence dimension.\n",
    "    Replaces mean pooling — learns which frames contain laughter.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Input:  (batch, seq_len, hidden_dim)\n",
    "    Output: (batch, hidden_dim)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    def __init__(self, hidden_dim: int):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.attention = torch.nn.Sequential(\n",
    "            torch.nn.Linear(hidden_dim, 128),\n",
    "            torch.nn.Tanh(),\n",
    "            torch.nn.Linear(128, 1),\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def forward(self, hidden_states):\n",
    "        # hidden_states: (batch, seq_len, hidden_dim)\n",
    "        scores = self.attention(hidden_states).squeeze(-1)  # (batch, seq_len)\n",
    "        weights = torch.nn.functional.softmax(scores, dim=1)  # (batch, seq_len)\n",
    "        weighted = weights.unsqueeze(-1) * hidden_states     # (batch, seq_len, hidden_dim)\n",
    "        pooled = weighted.sum(dim=1)                         # (batch, hidden_dim)\n",
    "        return pooled, weights  # return weights for analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4️⃣ Engram Module (information compression bottleneck)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Neuroscience inspiration**: An \"engram\" is the physical trace of a memory in the brain. \n",
    "\n",
    "**ML analogue**: Force the model to compress audio representations through a \n",
    "narrow bottleneck. This forces the encoder to learn DENSE, laughter-specific features\n",
    "rather than relying on sparse acoustic patterns.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "WavLM_hidden (batch, T, 768)\n",
    "  → AttentionPooling → (batch, 768)\n",
    "  → EngramBottleneck → (batch, 128)   # aggressive compression 768→256→128\n",
    "  → Audio features ready for fusion\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why this helps**: A 5-second audio window has ~80,000 samples. Mean pooling\n",
    "all 500 WavLM frames to 768-dim preserves too much noise. The bottleneck forces\n",
    "the model to keep only the laughter-predictive dimensions.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Bottleneck design**: \n",
    "  - 768 → 256 → 128 (two-stage compression)\n",
    "  - Residual connection: engram = Engram(attn_pooled) + proj(attn_pooled)\n",
    "  - This ensures the compression doesn't lose critical information"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class EngramModule(torch.nn.Module):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Information compression bottleneck inspired by memory engrams.\n",
    "    Forces dense laughter-specific encoding through a narrow bottleneck.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Architecture:\n",
    "      768 → 256 (geLU) → 128\n",
    "      + skip connection: output = Engram(compressed) + linear(768→128)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    The residual connection ensures compression doesn't lose critical info.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    def __init__(self, input_dim=768, bottleneck_dim=128):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.bottleneck = torch.nn.Sequential(\n",
    "            torch.nn.Linear(input_dim, 256),\n",
    "            torch.nn.GELU(),\n",
    "            torch.nn.Dropout(0.1),\n",
    "            torch.nn.Linear(256, bottleneck_dim),\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        # Skip connection: projects input directly to bottleneck_dim\n",
    "        self.skip = torch.nn.Linear(input_dim, bottleneck_dim)\n",
    "        self.layer_norm = torch.nn.LayerNorm(bottleneck_dim)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        compressed = self.bottleneck(x)\n",
    "        skipped    = self.skip(x)\n",
    "        engram     = self.layer_norm(compressed + skipped)\n",
    "        return engram"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5️⃣ Compressed Sparse Attention (CSA)\n",
    "\n",
    "**For audio**: 5 seconds = 500 WavLM frames (at 16kHz / 32 = 500Hz)\n",
    "Not long enough for standard CSA, BUT we can use CSA to attend to\n",
    "RARE high-energy / high-F0 frames that are more likely to contain laughter.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Simplified audio-CSA**: Instead of learnable sparse attention (expensive),\n",
    "use a lightweight two-stage approach:\n",
    "1. Compute per-frame energy + spectral features (cheap, no backprop)\n",
    "2. Select top-K (K=50) most \"laughter-like\" frames by heuristic score\n",
    "3. Attend only to those K frames via attention pooling\n",
    "\n",
    "This is a **hard attention** variant — faster and more interpretable.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Frame scoring**: energy * spectral_centroid_relevance * temporal_sparsity\n",
    "\n",
    "**Alternative (soft attention CSA)**: Learn a small number of \"basis vectors\"\n",
    "via a convolutional filter bank, then attend to top-N channels."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class CompressedSparseAttention(torch.nn.Module):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Audio-specific CSA: selects top-K informative frames before pooling.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Heuristic scoring (no backprop needed):\n",
    "      1. Per-frame energy (L2 norm of mel spectrogram)\n",
    "      2. Spectral centroid (perceptual brightness)\n",
    "      3. Zero-crossing rate (voicing)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    K=50 frames out of T=500 is 10:1 compression ratio.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    def __init__(self, hidden_dim=768, k_frames=50, n_mels=40):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.k_frames = k_frames\n",
    "        self.n_mels = n_mels\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Learnable frame scoring network\n",
    "        self.frame_scorer = torch.nn.Sequential(\n",
    "            torch.nn.Linear(hidden_dim, 64),\n",
    "            torch.nn.ReLU(),\n",
    "            torch.nn.Linear(64, 1),\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        # Attention pooling over selected frames\n",
    "        self.attn_pool = AttentionPooling(hidden_dim)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def forward(self, hidden_states, audio_waveform=None):\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        hidden_states: (batch, T, hidden_dim)\n",
    "        audio_waveform: (batch, T, n_mels) — mel spectrogram frames (optional)\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        # Step 1: Score all frames\n",
    "        frame_scores = self.frame_scorer(hidden_states).squeeze(-1)  # (batch, T)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Step 2: Top-K selection per example\n",
    "        batch_size, T = frame_scores.shape\n",
    "        topk_vals, topk_idx = torch.topk(frame_scores, k=min(self.k_frames, T), dim=1)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Step 3: Gather selected frame hidden states\n",
    "        # topk_idx: (batch, K), need to expand for gather\n",
    "        batch_indices = torch.arange(batch_size, device=hidden_states.device)\n",
    "        batch_indices = batch_indices[:, None].expand_as(topk_idx)  # (batch, K)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        selected = hidden_states[batch_indices, topk_idx]  # (batch, K, hidden_dim)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Step 4: Attention pool over selected frames\n",
    "        pooled, attn_weights = self.attn_pool(selected)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Also return raw scores for analysis\n",
    "        return pooled, attn_weights, topk_idx"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 6️⃣ MLA (Multi-Head Latent Attention) — optional variant\n",
    "# For audio, we use a simplified version: multi-head attention pooling\n",
    "# where each head focuses on different acoustic aspects.\n",
    "\n",
    "class MultiHeadLatentAttentionPooling(torch.nn.Module):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Simplified MLA for audio encoding.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Each head computes attention over the sequence independently,\n",
    "    capturing different acoustic aspects of laughter:\n",
    "      Head 0: Energy/amplitude patterns\n",
    "      Head 1: Pitch/F0 contours  \n",
    "      Head 2: Spectral content (MFCC-like)\n",
    "      Head 3: Temporal dynamics (delta features)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    These are not explicitly separated — the model learns to specialize.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    def __init__(self, hidden_dim=768, n_heads=4, k_frames=50):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        assert hidden_dim % n_heads == 0\n",
    "        self.n_heads = n_heads\n",
    "        self.head_dim = hidden_dim // n_heads\n",
    "        self.k_frames = k_frames\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Per-head projections (low-rank, like MLA)\n",
    "        self.q_proj = torch.nn.Linear(hidden_dim, hidden_dim)  # query\n",
    "        self.k_proj = torch.nn.Linear(hidden_dim, hidden_dim)  # key\n",
    "        self.v_proj = torch.nn.Linear(hidden_dim, hidden_dim)  # value\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Output projection\n",
    "        self.out_proj = torch.nn.Linear(hidden_dim, hidden_dim)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Per-head scoring for CSA selection\n",
    "        self.head_scorers = torch.nn.ModuleList([\n",
    "            torch.nn.Sequential(\n",
    "                torch.nn.Linear(self.head_dim, 32),\n",
    "                torch.nn.ReLU(),\n",
    "                torch.nn.Linear(32, 1)\n",
    "            ) for _ in range(n_heads)\n",
    "        ])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def forward(self, hidden_states):\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        hidden_states: (batch, T, hidden_dim)\n",
    "        Returns: (batch, hidden_dim) — pooled representation\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        B, T, D = hidden_states.shape\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Project to Q, K, V\n",
    "        Q = self.q_proj(hidden_states)  # (B, T, D)\n",
    "        K = self.k_proj(hidden_states)\n",
    "        V = self.v_proj(hidden_states)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Reshape into heads\n",
    "        Q = Q.view(B, T, self.n_heads, self.head_dim).transpose(1, 2)  # (B, H, T, d)\n",
    "        K = K.view(B, T, self.n_heads, self.head_dim).transpose(1, 2)\n",
    "        V = V.view(B, T, self.n_heads, self.head_dim).transpose(1, 2)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Scaled dot-product attention per head\n",
    "        scale = self.head_dim ** -0.5\n",
    "        attn_scores = torch.matmul(Q, K.transpose(-2, -1)) * scale  # (B, H, T, T)\n",
    "        attn_weights = F.softmax(attn_scores, dim=-1)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Weighted sum over values\n",
    "        head_outputs = torch.matmul(attn_weights, V)  # (B, H, T, d)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Concatenate heads back\n",
    "        concat_out = head_outputs.transpose(1, 2).contiguous().view(B, T, D)  # (B, T, D)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Final output projection\n",
    "        out = self.out_proj(concat_out)  # (B, T, D)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Mean pool over time\n",
    "        pooled = out.mean(dim=1)  # (B, D)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return pooled, attn_weights.mean(dim=1)  # return avg attn for analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
